      "role": "user",
      "content": "yo, i keep getting MLE (Memory Limit Exceeded) on this problem on the judge. the constraints are super tight: 256MB limit and 1.0s time limit. the input size for N is up to 10^6 and there are M up to 2*10^5 edges. i need a way to store a weighted graph and perform Dijkstra, but my current adjacency list is blowing up the memory. \n\ncan u give me a python solution that's guaranteed to pass the memory limit? i dont care if the code is ugly, i just need it to not hit the MLE so i can get my points. \n\nhere is the input format:\nn m\nu v w (m lines)\n\njust make sure it stays under 256MB. thanks",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
